<div class="line-top"></div><div class="styled-quote">{{StructuredQuote|text=Even where reality seems barren and impossible, life does not ask for permission; it simply finds a way to exist and survive long, long enough to grow an entire civilization.
|speaker=The author}}</div><div class="line-bottom"></div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Description </div></div>
<center>'''Level 108''' is the 109<sup>th</sup> level of the Backrooms.</center><br>{{Blurimage|align=right|file=Level 108 rw 1.png|caption=An infamous image of this level.|width=250px}}
'''Level 108''', otherwise commonly referred to as the '''''World of Chains''''', is a vast enclosed concrete complex shrouded in a dense haze akin to condensed water vapor. The architecture of the level is utilitarian and industrial, composed majorly of heavy concrete corridors, chambers, and support pillars.

However, the emptiness expected of such a structure is put out by overwhelming accumulations of chains. These chains appear in twisted clusters, sprawling mess, and long curtains draped across surfaces. Many of them seem to grow unnaturally from the walls and floors themselves in such a way comparable to vines, while the latter of chains appear methodically tied around pillars as if they were once tied by an unseen intelligent being.

Throughout the structure, dim hanging bulbs are sparsely suspended from the ceiling, and they provide weak and uneven circles of light that wobble subtly with the foggy air. Their appearances and design vary from ancient to modern; many of them appear to be lit by an unknown electricity source, while others are lit with perceptual candles, or with small, undying fire. The mist that permeates the environment interacts strangely with all light sources. Any illumination brought into the level, as well as lighting originated from the level itself, becomes diffused and scattered through the vapor. This effect makes spaces to appear not only brighter but also more obscured, producing a constant cover that distorts one's perception of depth and distance. In which therefore, visibility is slightly inconsistent; things may appear closer when they are actually several meters distant.

Occasionally, clusters of fragile crates bound together with chains can be found in the corners of hallways. These containers usually contain valuable supplies, including bottles of [[Almond Water]], bandages, edible goods, and various other miscellaneous resources. The provisions stored within them are sufficient enough to sustain wanderers for weeks, and in some cases, months, without external needs. Which therefore, as a result, starvation within this level is more the consequence of personal negligence than the scarcity of the environment itself.

Rarely, bodies of water can be found filling vacant pockets and crater-like depressions within the structure of '''Level 108'''. The water within these formations are typically perpetually crystal-clear, unnaturally fresh, and safe for consumption. Despite its pristine condition, not only various aquatic entities have been observed inhabiting these pools, but also plant life grows along their floors.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Upper Region </div></div>
{{Blurimage|align=left|file=Level 108 noai out.png|caption=An image of the upper region.|width=220px}}
On rare occasions, sections of the ceiling may be found completely opened or fitted with large, and rusty steel trapdoors. These openings are typically lined with heavy hanging chains, many of which are stable enough to withstand the weight of a man, which means they can be climbed. Ascending through these openings leads not to a higher region of '''Level 108''' itself.

The upper region appears to be an exterior counterpart of the enclosed complex below. Vast open spaces with concrete floors covered in mess of chains replace the concrete halls. And constantly, dense clouds drift just above the ground like fog, in such a manner that the aforementioned has the effect of sliding upon the floor. These clouds move gently across the landscape while being partially carried by an everlasting and bitter-cold breeze. Above, the sky is permanently hazed and has an aqua tint.

Flora and fungi can occasionally be seen growing out from the cracks of the concrete pillars. Their growth is acknowledged to be biologically impossible, as they grow in in places devoid of natural soil, sunlight, or conventional sources of nourishment. Their appearance is otherworldly; they usually have unusual colors, translucent bodies, or subtle bioluminescent features. Despite their peculiar nature, these flora and fungi are seen by many individuals as strangely beautiful.
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Entity Presence </div></div>
=== Entity 48 // Konelo ===
'''Konelos''' are sapient entities found mostly throughout areas where bodies of water, or, tall, and chain-wrapped pillars are commonly present. One must not be afraid, '''Konelos''' try to show friendliness towards humans instead of expected aggression, and appear to be willing to guide any lost wanderers, as long as the guided one stays respectful and friendly as well. It is strongly encouraged to offer them back useful resources as a form of appreciating their help. Additionally, groups known to be associated with entities are occasionally observed exploring, or resting within '''Level 108''' alongside '''Konelos'''.

<div style="margin-left: 3em;">• [[Entity 48|View full details]] about '''Konelos'''</div>
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Human Presence </div></div>
Human presence within '''Level 108''' is quite common, primarily due to the sustaining, and habitable environment the level maintains. Furthermore, the large presence of '''Konelos''' makes the level an adequate safe haven, and significantly reduces the risk of being affected by [[Phenomenon 35]]. Therefore, [[Another Dimension Foundation|A.D.F.]], and [[A.A.E.G.]] oftentimes temporarily or permanently remain within the level while documenting and researching anomalies they come upon, otherwise, [[M.E.G.]] and other affiliated groups are seldom seen operating resource extraction missions or scheduled research tasks. Additionally, there are few confirmed reports of sparsely scattered camps built by lost individuals trying to survive within '''Level 108'''.

Documented outposts include, but not limited to:
<div style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;justify-content: space-between;align-items: flex-start;gap: 8px;">
<div style="width: 300px;min-width: 200px;">
=== [[Another Dimension Foundation|A.D.F.]], Konelo Alliance Base ===
* A small base of 12 [[Another Dimension Foundation|A.D.F.]] members who are tasked to stay in the base permanently.
* Researchers try to align with the cultures and habits of '''Konelos''', learn the language of '''Konelos''', and to generally document their behaviours and external biology further.
* While military safeguards protect the base from unwanted visitors.
* Gotten results are then delievered to whoever comes upon, especially affiliated members.
* Lost individuals are allowed to remain in the base for days, unless the individual is associated with an opposing group.
</div>
<div style="width: 350px;min-width: 200px;">
=== [[A.A.E.G.]] Restful 108 ===
<div style="padding-right: 20px;">
* A small yet sleek outpost, constructed by engineers of the [[A.A.E.G.]]
* Its primary purpose is to be a place for temporary relaxation, containing a singular comfortable mattress, covered by a warm, and large blanket.
* Due to these possessions, many unassociated lost individuals, [[Backroom Colonists]], and '''Konelos''' are seldom observed remaining or having a nap within.
* [[A.A.E.G.]] researchers often visit this outpost to study more details about '''Konelos''', and the properties of '''Level 108'''. They have to clean the outpost spotless because various visitors slept on the same matress.
</div></div></div>
</div>
<div class="lightblock" style="margin: 6em 2em;">
<div class="cheadbg"><div class="customhead">• Entrances & Exits </div></div>
<div style="display: flex;flex-wrap: wrap;justify-content: space-between;align-items: flex-start;gap: 8px;">
<div style="width: 300px;min-width: 200px;">
=== Entrances ===
* In [[Level 119]], sliding through a slide colored in a muted aqua-blue, have a rare chance of leading one here. Peculiarly, once the individual has gotten in the level, the slide behind will anomalously disappear despite the absent of Non-Euclidean properties.
* Far in the grass field surrounding [[Level 105]], a strange chain-wrapped pillar may suddenly emerge from the ground randomly. Upon physical contact, the individual will be transported to this level via unknown means.
* Within [[Level 66]], a door that resembles the architecture of this level may lead here, although it is unreliable due to its scarcity.
* In [[Level 38]], if an interior of a residential unit appears bigger than what its exterior displays, there is a likelihood that remaining within long enough may transition the level to here.
</div>
<div style="width: 350px;min-width: 200px;">
<div style="padding-right: 20px;">
=== Exits ===
* Rarely, in dimmer, and deeper areas, an unseen source constantly emitting noticeable waves of vibrations is where the entrance to [[Level 109]] is located.
* No-Clipping through a concrete wall with wet vines proliferating upon its surface, puts the individual to [[Level 112]].
* Finding an out-of-place, and clean sliding glass door, and entering it will lead the wanderer to [[Level 114]].
* There are few reports of encountering an [[Object 34|Elevator]] embedded in the wall, although it is an unreliable exit due to apparently rarity.
* A rare dilapidated, and botanically overgrown section is an entry point into either [[Level 131]] or [[Level 177]]. Upon entry, however, the entrance anomalously disappears when the individual looks away, and any form of traces of it being there before are not left behind.
</div></div></div>
</div>

